{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1771863724,"nonce":"9furugS1ZgZMuyN8Rm0uCagWDt4=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87rMBVl","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-3945796965"},"message":"One example of how I am working today: In one claude code console, I am working on a complex problem of redesigning the workspace, so most of my attention is there. In a separate console, I am reviewing CI files to identify packages missing basic testing and worikng on adding those.\n\nHaving a task I can periodically add feedback to without much deep thought works well while working on one where I need to focus on more.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1771870603,"nonce":"ftVR5pQXODYpsxFqwAsQ6pebBfU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87rOm0I","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-3946474760"},"message":"One observation, having agent interns pushes me to adopt software engineering practices that would be too heavy and add to much friction for solo develoment. Having agents take care of that friction allows me to gain their benefits while reducing their costs.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772053958,"nonce":"EG94DV5y6o4tahB3Ls0S6KtRpsg=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sKQbc","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-3962111708"},"message":"Having agents working on issues allows me to  better context switch and multitask. By not having to hold all the details in my head, I can address something in one part of the code, then when I swtich back to another task I was working on, I can simply ask the agent to refresh my memory if needed, and that is seldom needed. It has allowed me to better persue ideas that could be distracting by quickly mentioning them to another agent instance, and coming back to it later to flesh it out, and have the agent open issues when appropriate. Previoulsy, doing something like that would have been too much of a distraction to what I was originally working on. Does that mean this workspace is customized for how my brain works or will it be helpful as eaqualy to others?","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772061411,"nonce":"7sP/gSSI6a1RNCaTwnQs/IXEeZA=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sM_zp","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-3962830057"},"message":"Being more integrated with GitHub allows me to brainstorm ideas on the go. For example, while waiting for my daughter to be done with gymnastics, I can, on my phone, open an issue, start chatting with an agent using the phone app about the issue, then add the summary of the chat as a comment on the issue.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772117545,"nonce":"Otez/yyow71gXrfNWFQVhKwpB2M=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sdZFl","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-3967127909"},"message":"The current effort is to implement skills to review workflows against the guiding principles and ADRs. It feels like I'm teaching toddler agents to become adult agents by imparting to them my wisdom and principles.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772457313,"nonce":"mEadWVKCnB7u6Czi8jQMSSNhmAo=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87tfAnW","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-3984329174"},"message":"This morning, Mar 2, 2026, claude code is down. I'll switch to copilot cli for the moment. This highlights one drawback of relying on an online LLM.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1772546617,"nonce":"XyKfdI607RmrVojWwKwQe7JarbQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOQ241x87tfAnWzp37x60"},"target":"5eb51235ea514c96b7e046735ebe9a6453125b40cdfbc8ba2cf753ddc106808c","message":"This morning, Mar 2, 2026, claude code is down. I'll switch to copilot cli for the moment. This highlights one drawback of relying on an online LLM.\n\nIt was a pleasant surprise when copilot cli recognized the claude skills as slash commands. The switch back to copilot wasn't as hard as I had feared after using claude almost exclusively for a few weeks. I did have to get used to slight differences in how permissions are requested, but I wasn't slowed down too much by the unexpected need to switch tools.\n\nInvestigating a local llm as an additional backup or primary tool is probably a good idea.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772683593,"nonce":"o8ro7NDFY8yRGnUUmHWGUkf7w44=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87uicZX","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/250#issuecomment-4002006615"},"message":"Today, it was GitHub slowing me down. Claude hit an API rate limit which has is pause GitHub interactions for about 30 minutes. We took the time to brainstorm how to make GitHub optional.","files":null}]}